JOHANNESBURG – The ANC's National Working Committee (NWC) has recommended that national party officials immediately meet with North West premier and ANC provincial chairperson Supra Mahumapelo to discuss the tensions in the province. It follows the NWC's ordinary meeting in Cape Town on Wednesday. The committee "considered the developments in the North West Province and reflected on the deep crisis in the NW Health Department and other departments in the province," it said in a statement. READ: 65 suspected looters in court following North West riots The North West Health Department has been put under administration. At the same time, the provincial capital Mahikeng was rocked by violent protests during April, as residents called on Mahumapelo to resign amid corruption allegations. WATCH: I welcome any probe against me: Supra Mahumapelo "The NWC welcomed the intervention of cabinet in the province which is aimed at restoring good governance and ensuring service delivery is not halted," the committee said. "The NWC recommended that the national officials immediately meet with the Premier of the North West Province, who is also the chairperson of the ANC in the province, to discuss all available constructive options to resolve the ongoing impasse in the interest of the people of the North West Province and the movement broadly." eNCA